    # Melt the DataFrame, reset index to keep track of original rows
    df = df.reset_index().melt(id_vars='index', var_name='column', value_name='value')
    
    # Split the column names into original column names and categories
    df[['column', 'category']] = df['column'].str.split('_', expand=True)
    
    # Filter out rows where value is 0
    df = df[df['value'] == 1]
    
    # Pivot the DataFrame back into its original form
    df = df.pivot(index='index', columns='column', values='category')
    
    # Reset the column names
    df.columns.name = None
    
    return df

import pandas as pd
def correct_function(data):
    data['Timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Timestamp'])
    data = data.sort_values(by=['User', 'Timestamp'])
    data['TimeDiff'] = data.groupby('User')['Timestamp'].diff()
    data['Session_ID'] = (data['TimeDiff'] > pd.Timedelta(minutes=30)).cumsum()
    data = data.drop('TimeDiff', axis=1)
    return data
